    "Alignment-based methods first align spans of the input text to AMR nodes using rule-based heuristics and then perform concept identification and relation extraction based on these alignments.In contrast, transition-based approaches generate AMRs incrementally by predicting a sequence of actions (e.g., shift,went the boy home nsubj advmod det.",
    "punct go-02 boy home ARG0 ARG4The boy went home.",
    "Transition-basedAlignment-based reduce, or arc operations) that build the graph structure, often guided by an intermediate dependency tree.",
    "Fig. 3 illustrates the core ideas behind these approaches.JAMR [32] is widely recognized as the first AMR parser that operates in a two-stage pipeline.",
    "First, it maps the concepts in the sentence to concept nodes in the graph using a rule-based semi-Markov model for sequence labeling.Then, it determines the relationships between these concepts by finding the highest-scoring connected subgraph."
